block directory

List block directory items

Query this endpoint to retrieve a collection of block directory items.

The response you receive can be controlled and filtered using the URL query parameters below.

query Parameters
context
any
Default: "view"
Value: "view"

Scope under which the request is made; determines fields present in response, limited to view.

page
number >= 1
Default: 1

Current page of the collection.

per_page
number [ 1 .. 100 ]
Default: 10

Maximum number of items to be returned in result set.

term
required
string non-empty

Limit result set to blocks matching the search term.

Responses

blocks

/wp/v2/blocks

query Parameters
context
any
Default: "view"
Enum: "view" "embed" "edit"

Scope under which the request is made; determines fields present in response.

page
number >= 1
Default: 1

Current page of the collection.

per_page
number [ 1 .. 100 ]
Default: 10

Maximum number of items to be returned in result set.

search
any

Limit results to those matching a string.

after
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts published after a given ISO8601 compliant date.

modified_after
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts modified after a given ISO8601 compliant date.

before
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts published before a given ISO8601 compliant date.

modified_before
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts modified before a given ISO8601 compliant date.

exclude
Array of integers

Ensure result set excludes specific IDs.

include
Array of integers

Limit result set to specific IDs.

search_semantics
any
Value: "exact"

How to interpret the search input.

offset
any

Offset the result set by a specific number of items.

order
any
Default: "desc"
Enum: "asc" "desc"

Order sort attribute ascending or descending.

orderby
any
Default: "date"
Enum: "author" "date" "id" "include" "modified" "parent" "relevance" "slug" "include_slugs" "title"

Sort collection by post attribute.

search_columns
Array of strings
Items Enum: "post_title" "post_content" "post_excerpt"

Array of column names to be searched.

slug
Array of strings

Limit result set to posts with one or more specific slugs.

status
Array of strings
Default: "publish"
Items Enum: "publish" "future" "draft" "pending" "private" "trash" "auto-draft" "inherit" "request-pending" "request-confirmed" "request-failed" "request-completed" "any"

Limit result set to posts assigned one or more statuses.

tax_relation
any
Enum: "AND" "OR"

Limit result set based on relationship between multiple taxonomies.

Array of Term ID List (integers) or Term ID Taxonomy Query (object)

Limit result set to items with specific terms assigned in the wp_pattern_category taxonomy.

Array of Term ID List (integers) or Term ID Taxonomy Query (object)

Limit result set to items except those with specific terms assigned in the wp_pattern_category taxonomy.

/wp/v2/media/{id}

path Parameters
id
required
any

Unique identifier for the post.

Request Body schema: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
date
string or null <date-time>

The date the post was published, in the site's timezone.

date_gmt
string or null <date-time>

The date the post was published, as GMT.

slug
string

An alphanumeric identifier for the post unique to its type.

status
string
Enum: "publish" "future" "draft" "pending" "private"

A named status for the post.

object

The title for the post.

author
integer

The ID for the author of the post.

featured_media
integer

The ID of the featured media for the post.

comment_status
string
Enum: "open" "closed"

Whether or not comments are open on the post.

ping_status
string
Enum: "open" "closed"

Whether or not the post can be pinged.

meta
object

Meta fields.

template
string

The theme file to use to display the post.

alt_text
string

Alternative text to display when attachment is not displayed.

object

The attachment caption.

object

The attachment description.

post
integer

The ID for the associated post of the attachment.

/wp/v2/media/{id}/edit

path Parameters
id
required
any
Request Body schema: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
src
required
string <uri>

URL to the edited image file.

Array of Rotation (object) or Crop (object) non-empty

Array of image edits.

rotation
integer [ 0 .. 360 ]

The amount to rotate the image clockwise in degrees. DEPRECATED: Use modifiers instead.

x
number [ 0 .. 100 ]

As a percentage of the image, the x position to start the crop from. DEPRECATED: Use modifiers instead.

y
number [ 0 .. 100 ]

As a percentage of the image, the y position to start the crop from. DEPRECATED: Use modifiers instead.

width
number [ 0 .. 100 ]

As a percentage of the image, the width to crop the image to. DEPRECATED: Use modifiers instead.

height
number [ 0 .. 100 ]

As a percentage of the image, the height to crop the image to. DEPRECATED: Use modifiers instead.

menu-items

/wp/v2/menu-items

query Parameters
context
any
Default: "view"
Enum: "view" "embed" "edit"

Scope under which the request is made; determines fields present in response.

page
number >= 1
Default: 1

Current page of the collection.

per_page
any
Default: 100

Maximum number of items to be returned in result set.

search
any

Limit results to those matching a string.

after
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts published after a given ISO8601 compliant date.

modified_after
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts modified after a given ISO8601 compliant date.

before
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts published before a given ISO8601 compliant date.

modified_before
any <date-time>

Limit response to posts modified before a given ISO8601 compliant date.

exclude
Array of integers

Ensure result set excludes specific IDs.

include
Array of integers

Limit result set to specific IDs.

search_semantics
any
Value: "exact"

How to interpret the search input.

offset
any

Offset the result set by a specific number of items.

order
any
Default: "asc"

Order sort attribute ascending or descending.

orderby
any
Default: "menu_order"
Enum: "author" "date" "id" "include" "modified" "parent" "relevance" "slug" "include_slugs" "title" "menu_order"

Sort collection by object attribute.

search_columns
Array of strings
Items Enum: "post_title" "post_content" "post_excerpt"

Array of column names to be searched.

slug
Array of strings

Limit result set to posts with one or more specific slugs.

status
Array of strings
Default: "publish"
Items Enum: "publish" "future" "draft" "pending" "private" "trash" "auto-draft" "inherit" "request-pending" "request-confirmed" "request-failed" "request-completed" "any"

Limit result set to posts assigned one or more statuses.

tax_relation
any
Enum: "AND" "OR"

Limit result set based on relationship between multiple taxonomies.

Array of Term ID List (integers) or Term ID Taxonomy Query (object)

Limit result set to items with specific terms assigned in the menus taxonomy.

Array of Term ID List (integers) or Term ID Taxonomy Query (object)

Limit result set to items except those with specific terms assigned in the menus taxonomy.

menu_order
any

Limit result set to posts with a specific menu_order value.

/wp/v2/menu-items

Request Body schema: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
string or object

The title for the object.

type
string
Default: "custom"
Enum: "taxonomy" "post_type" "post_type_archive" "custom"

The family of objects originally represented, such as "post_type" or "taxonomy".

status
string
Default: "publish"
Enum: "publish" "future" "draft" "pending" "private"

A named status for the object.

parent
integer >= 0
Default: 0

The ID for the parent of the object.

attr_title
string

Text for the title attribute of the link element for this menu item.

classes
Array of strings

Class names for the link element of this menu item.

description
string

The description of this menu item.

menu_order
integer >= 1
Default: 1

The DB ID of the nav_menu_item that is this item's menu parent, if any, otherwise 0.

object
string

The type of object originally represented, such as "category", "post", or "attachment".

object_id
integer >= 0
Default: 0

The database ID of the original object this menu item represents, for example the ID for posts or the term_id for categories.

target
string
Enum: "_blank" ""

The target attribute of the link element for this menu item.

url
string <uri>

The URL to which this menu item points.

xfn
Array of strings

The XFN relationship expressed in the link of this menu item.

menus
integer

The terms assigned to the object in the nav_menu taxonomy.

meta
object

Meta fields.
